abstract: HEMPSTEAD, N.Y., Nov. 6. -- Mrs. Adolf Ladenburg came a nasty cropper while following the Meadow Brook hounds to-day. abstract: ITHACA, N.Y., Nov. 17. -- Cornell easily defeated the heavy Swarthmore eleven this afternoon by the score of 28 to 0. abstract: THE men who dredge and tong the oysters from the Chesapeake Bay bottoms sometimes find strange things in their catches. Two years ago, at the mouth of Secretary Creek, on Big Choptank River, a tonger was fishing the rock near the creek buoy when he found a curious lump among the shells. It was apparently a porous Stone five or six inches long and three inches thick -- the shape of a common cobble.

abstract: POSEN, Prussia, Nov. 29. -- All last night the body of Mgr. Stablewski, Archbishop of Posen, who died Nov. 24, lay in state in the cathedral here, the ancient burial place of the Polish Kings, and throughout the night a procession of people passed through the building. The Poles are intensely excited over the expectation that the Prussian Government will veto the nomination of any prelate except a German.
